          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 252Cf was prepared from 239Pu by successive",
                "neutron-capture and beta-decay reactions in the",
                "Materials Testing Reactor. The 252Cf (2.4 x 10-3",
                "microg) was chemically purified and electroplated as",
                "a uniform thin deposit on a 0.002 in. thick gold foil",
                "in an area of 0.05 cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "REC",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The energies of the incident helium",
                "ions were reduced to the desired values with",
                "aluminium absorbers. The recoil products were",
                "collected on gold foils of about 5 mg/cm2 thickness.",
                "The gold was dissolved in a mixture of hydrochloric",
                "and nitric acids. The fermium, einsteinium and",
                "californium isotopes were identified by measurements",
                "of their decay properties in an ionization-grid",
                "chamber with a forty-eight channel alpha-particle",
                "pulse-height analyzer. The decay of the various",
                "alpha-particle peaks was usually followed through",
                "several half-lives."
              ]
            }
          ],
